    <h1>Questions, Questions, Questions, flooding into the mind of the concerned young person today...</h1>

  <h2>Why can't I post anything?</h2>

  <p>If you don't see the "compose" link in the navigation, you probably logged in with an account that didn't end in @colby.edu.</p>

  <p><strong>Updated 9/2/12:</strong> we now have a fix for this.</p>

  <p>If you're a Colby student who uses a separate Gmail account as your primary email, you're going to have to do the following (open each sequentially in a new tab):</p>

  <ol>
    <li><a href="https://www.google.com/accounts/Logout">Log out of Gmail/Google</a></li>
    <li><a href="/logout">Log out of The Better Announcements</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://gmail.com">Log back into Gmail/Google with your Colby account</a></li>
    <li><a href="/">Log back into The Better Announcements</a></li>
  </ol>

  <p>Once you're done with that, you'll be so good at logging you'd make a smashing addition to the woodsmen team.</p>

  <h2>Can I sign in without using my Google account?</h2>

  <p>Currently the only way to create an account on The Better Announcements is to login using your Google account. Since @colby.edu accounts are technically Google accounts, this covers 100% of the people we want to help.</p>

  <h2>What if I only want your announcements?</h2>

  <p>If you're ready to take this relationship to the next level, you can <a href="http://www.colby.edu/administration_cs/its/services/notices/unsubscribe.cfm">unsubscribe from the general announcements.</a> If you're not ready to do that yet, that's cool, we can still be friends.</p>

  <h2>How many Colby students are on The Better Announcements?</h2>

  <p>Between 0 and 1825.</p>

  <h2>Jeff, I see you using cool formatting in your posts. How can I be like you?</h2>

  <p>All posts are formatted using <a href="">Markdown</a>. I plan on making this more clear on the site soon.</p>

